HEADWORD: Madeira vine
<hw>Ma*dei"ra vine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
herbaceous climbing vine (<spn>Boussingaultia baselloides</spn>) very
popular in cultivation, having shining entire leaves and racemes of
small fragrant white flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

